From Europe he has pressed the promise for another 5,000, even if he himself originally calculated at least 10,000.
Highly problematic for the Obama strategy as a whole is his plan to withdraw troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and complete this process within three years. Obama ’ s doctrine leaves more questions than answers.
Some doubt that the halved increase will have the same effect as the measure in Iraq.
Even in spite of the fratricidal war of the last years, Iraq is relatively well structured, its leaders honor the values.
The Afghan situation is characterised by contraindication - no one can be relied upon and no agreements are made.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, who are accustomed to changing their minds every day.
The political institutions, even if they were formally founded correctly, remain only pseudo-buildings behind which the patriarchal ancestral relations will continue to grow.
The balance of interests between the various ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the unclarity of the conditions that further complicate Pakistan and Iran ’ s influences.
It is also very unrealistic to build a "state capable of action", which is the minimalist objective of the whole operation.
Obama ’ s time horizon strategy alienated by his voluntarism
