The work of the experts of three institutes of the Academy of Sciences CR, of the VSCHT (Chemical Technological University) Prague as well as of the University of Heidelberg opens the way, how one can deal with the virus's resistance.
They have shown that the substances referred to as metalokarborane act on the protein substance responsible for the propagation of the HIV viral.
Metalokarborans are compounds of boron, hydrogen, carbon and cobalt.
These compounds block the virus ’ s proliferation in a way other than all medicines used today, which is why they can overcome the resistance issue.
In their work, the scientists arrive at new 'improved' compounds which were prepared on the basis of the knowledge of the molecular mechanism of their binding on the viruses of protein.
The metallic carborans have a unique three-dimensional structure: two multifaceted cages consisting of boron, hydrogen and carbon atoms and coupled by a metal atom, in this case cobalt.
