The problem is money.
Other couples give psychological reasons for their hesitation.
Wang, the Human Resources Manager, said she wanted only one child because she was also a single child. "We were the center of the family and used to care for each one of us.
We are not used to taking care of others and do not really want to. "
Chen Zijian, a 42 year old to whom a translation company belongs, said it more bluntly.
For parents from the middle class with double careers, through which the birth rate decreases, he said, it turns to be successful and for this one must be selfish.
The age group of today ’ s 20- to 39-year-olds grew up struggling to see their parents fight during the early days of China ’ s capitalism experiment, and they don ’ t want such a life for themselves, he said.
Even a single child, he said, places huge demands on the time of parents.
