According to Eduardo Velázquez, Sales Manager of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers work together, each of them providing the information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is increasing, to the point that over the last five years more versions, variants and motorization have been launched than in the previous fifteen years.
As soon as a new car enters the market, work begins for the companies.
It is a laborious task, because each individual of the thousands of vehicle parts must be catagolized and its price entered.
In addition, each model creates an "intelligent" graphic image on which you can "click" different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a much sold model, the work can be completed in one week if the procedure proceeds quickly.
If it is a less common car, it can take up to three or four months. Currently, Audatex has 99.2% of the cars sold in Spain with full information.
Among the more exclusive models, for example, they have information about the Porsche models, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the vehicle fleet driving on the roads, it is more than 99%.
In order to carry out the documentation work and the production of databases, Audatex has eight worldwide distributed centres (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in certain brands.
The national headquarters are located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanical experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million euros annually in the development of these databases.
Every month they collect 2.5 million data and their customers receive updates every second day.
The development of this enormous flow of information enables companies to use it in different ways and thus offer different products.
The most common use is the use for repairs and repairs, but depending on the country there are also tools for managing scrap parts or for calculating the file or residual value of a car.
